&lt;p&gt;Manchester University NHS Foundation Trust (MFT) is one of the largest acute Trusts in the UK, employing over 20,000 staff and incorporating nine hospitals across six separate sites. Providing a wide range of services from comprehensive local general hospital care through to highly specialised regional and national services, we are the main provider of hospital care to approximately 750,000 people in the Manchester and Trafford area and are the single biggest provider of specialised services in the North West of England.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic, motivated individual with substantial administrative experience to join our friendly Informatics Team within the Critical Care Department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will have strong organisational skills, attention to detail and a commitment to delivering a high quality service. You will be able to use your own initiative to prioritise and manage workload effectively to meet deadlines and have excellent verbal and written communication skills. You will be able to work both within a team and autonomously and be IT literate with experience of using databases.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
